LUMPY SKIN DISEASE - BULGARIA (05): BOVINE, INTERNATIONAL IMPLICATIONS
**********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this posting:
[1] Bulgaria, spread
[2] International trade implications: Romania, Turkey

******
[1] Bulgaria, spread
Date: Sat 23 Apr 2016
Source: Focus News Agency [edited]
http://www.focus-fen.net/news/2016/04/23/404501/15-lumpy-skin-disease-outbreaks-in-bulgaria-disinfection-started.html


"There are 15 lumpy skin disease outbreaks. The territory we have outlined with the Ministry of Agriculture and Food for disinfection spraying covers the affected settlements in the districts of Stara Zagora and Haskovo," said Dr Georgi Chobanov, director of the Healthcare, Humane Approach towards Animals and Fodder Control Directorate with the Bulgarian Food Safety Agency, speaking for FOCUS News Agency, commenting on the disinfection spraying against the disease.

According to him, a circle of a 30 km [about 19 mile] radius has been outlined around each outbreak.

